cleanDesc: QuickJack BL-5000SLX Vehicle Lift - 5,000 Lb. Capacity
short-description: Working in the garage with a jack and jack stands can be a pain, but most people don't have the space for a full size lift. QuickJack sought to solve this issue and has developed an extensive line of lifts and accessories for any type of vehicle. Unlike traditional lifts that are mounted to the floor permanently, QuickJack lifts are ultra-portable and lightweight, easily transported from home to the track and back in your back seat, trunk, or in your truck bed. Plus, when needed, are significantly faster to use than a jack and jack stands. Just plug in the power connection and within a matter of seconds, you can lift your vehicle 20+ inches off of the ground. Also, unlike jack stands that can be unsteady at significant heights, the QuickJack Vehicle Lift System is very stable. Using rugged welded steel construction and auto-locking safety bars, these lifts will resist the toughest real-world garage and track conditions, resisting excessive movement. If the worst were to happen and something failed while you were underneath of the vehicle, the high strength safety bars will stay locked in position, holding up your vehicle and preventing you from any negative outcomes. The last major feature of the QuickJack Vehicle Lift System is that there are no crossbeams in the center. This opens up the underside of your vehicle for drivetrain, exhaust, and suspension services.

cleanDesc: Aluminum Jack Pad Adapter for E46/E9X Jack Pads
short-description: Your floor jack is universal but it doesn't have to be with this adapter! Most newer BMW jack pads have an open recess inside that this adapter fits into. It's a rectangular peg for a rectangular hole. This gives the jack a much more rigid connection and almost impossible for the jack or pad to slip. You will never have to worry about scratching your rocker panels or jacking from the wrong spot - the positive connection ensures you are always lifting from the correct location. This adapter is one of those small hidden gems that you can't live without!

Many BMWs, especially older models, feature pinch welds where the floor pan meets the rocker. These run from wheel-well-to-wheel-well and are an especially appealing jacking location with one shortfall - jacking on an unprotected pinch weld will frequently cause an unsightly bent and damaged weld. This damage is a quick to rust spot, being located on the lowest point of the vehicle and no longer being covered by protective ecoat, paint, or undercoat.
